  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7 ! \u0b95\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bcb\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u00a0\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc7 ?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Prisoners are also human! Where is the fault in Kantakadu tragedy?",
      "author": "Presath",
      "body_lines": [
        "Travelers traveling to Borella via the Colombo Baseline may have seen the slogan 'Prisoners are Humans' as they pass the Welikada Prison. What we are saying now is that the rehabilitated are also human.",
        "After the end of the war, a rehabilitation center was started in Kantagadu area of \u200b\u200bPolonnaruwa. The LTTE members were rehabilitated. The program later became a drug addiction rehabilitation center. It became a covid treatment center during the covid era. Then again it became a place to rehabilitate drug addicts. Nearly a thousand people have been rehabilitated there.",
        "From the night of last 28th, Kantagadu became the talking point all over the country.",
        "There was a commotion at Kantagadu Rehabilitation Center when an inmate had tobacco in his possession. Although tobacco is not a prohibited type, tobacco is prohibited in the land as it is a drug addiction rehabilitation center.",
        "Accordingly, possession of tobacco by a rehabilitated inmate is certainly grounds for proper investigation. Because any prisoner is admitted to the rehabilitation center only after thorough examination.",
        "Also, the inmates are not allowed to take anything from home and the necessary clothes and all other things have to be provided from the center. The question is how a prisoner could bring tobacco in such an environment.",
        "The prisoner who had the tobacco was found dead at dawn the next day. The cause of death is pending investigation. But other inmates claim the death was due to assault. Several news outlets reported that the military attributed the death to a clash between prisoners.",
        "After the prisoner's death, about six hundred people were reported to have escaped from the camp, and the police and army were able to recapture more than five hundred of them. The rioters also reportedly damaged the property and vehicles of the rehabilitation center. The security forces were reportedly attacked with stones and the prisoners marched into Somavati Park.",
        "The inmates of Kanthakad Rehabilitation Center are drug addicts. And such persons are sent to the center on court orders. Therefore, it is questionable whether there are people who willingly go to rehab.",
        "Therefore, these prisoners should be treated as special prisoners. With drug addicts, their mindset is different. It takes some time for those minds to recover through a rehabilitation process. Therefore, special attention should be paid to them. Since rehabilitation is central, psychologists should be recruited.",
        "According to media reports, the rehabilitation center is run under the Commissioner General's Department of Rehabilitation and security is being provided by the military outside the central station. It is clear from the recent broadcasts regarding this center that a very positive atmosphere prevailed.",
        "A large group of rehabilitated prisoners jumping into a park is no easy feat. The impact they will have on people's lives is unpredictable. Also, keeping in mind that such behavior may emerge from the inmates, security measures should have been strengthened to leave no room for lapses.",
        "Two army personnel and two air force personnel have been remanded in connection with the incident.",
        "The Commissioner General of Rehabilitation had said that according to the postmortem report of the deceased prisoner, he was acting impartially. If the officials commit any wrongdoing, the law will be enforced against them irrespective of their status."
      ],
